---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Terms of Service | ClubShed';
const description = 'The rules for using ClubShed. Plain language, no hidden clauses. What we provide, what we expect, what happens if things go wrong.';
const lastUpdated = '2026-06-18';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">

      <header class="legal-page__header">
        <span class="tag">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="display">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-page__updated">Last updated: 18 June 2026</p>
      </header>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>The short version</h2>
        <p>ClubShed is software for tracking football equipment. By signing up you agree to use it for its intended purpose, not break it on purpose, and pay for any paid plan you sign up to. We promise to keep the service running as best we reasonably can and to handle your data with respect.</p>
        <p>If something goes badly wrong, our liability is limited to what you paid us in the last 12 months. That's standard for SaaS and it cuts both ways.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>ClubShed is operated by Lucas Seewald, based in Spain. Contact: <a href="mailto:hello@clubshed.pro">hello@clubshed.pro</a>. These Terms govern your use of clubshed.pro (the marketing site) and app.clubshed.pro (the application).</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>What we provide</h2>
        <p>ClubShed is a web-based software service for tracking sports equipment, allocating items to teams, tracking conditions, and generating reports. We offer the service on a free tier (1 team, 30 items, 3 coaches) and a paid Club plan (€15.99 per month, unlimited usage).</p>
        <p>We provide the service "as is" and on an "as available" basis. We aim for high uptime but we don't guarantee zero downtime. We may make changes to features over time; significant changes that remove existing functionality will be communicated to paid users in advance.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Your account</h2>
        <p>You're responsible for the accuracy of the information you provide when signing up, for keeping your password secure, and for activity that happens under your account. If you suspect unauthorised access, email us at <a href="mailto:hello@clubshed.pro">hello@clubshed.pro</a>.</p>
        <p>You must be at least 16 years old to create an account. Football clubs are run by adults; the service isn't directed at children.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use ClubShed for anything illegal, abusive, or harmful to others</li>
          <li>Try to reverse engineer, scrape, or otherwise extract source code or data not belonging to you</li>
          <li>Probe, test, or breach our security measures (we have an open invitation for legitimate security researchers to email us instead)</li>
          <li>Resell, sublicense, or commercialise ClubShed as your own product</li>
          <li>Upload content that infringes someone else's copyright or rights</li>
          <li>Use the service to send spam or unsolicited messages</li>
        </ul>
        <p>If you do any of these we may suspend or terminate your account. We'll usually warn you first unless the issue is severe.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Your data and content</h2>
        <p>Your data stays your data. We never claim ownership of equipment lists, team rosters, photos, or any information you upload. You grant us a limited licence to host and process that data only for the purpose of running the service for you.</p>
        <p>You can export your full inventory as CSV at any time. You can delete your account at any time, which removes all your data within 30 days. The details of how we handle data are in the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Paid plans, billing, and refunds</h2>
        <p>The Club plan is €15.99 per month, billed monthly via Stripe. Subscriptions renew automatically until cancelled. You can cancel at any time from your billing settings; you'll keep paid features until the end of the current billing period.</p>
        <p>We offer a 14-day no-card-required trial on the Club plan. If you don't add a card by the end of the trial, the account rolls back to the Free plan automatically. No charges are ever made without your explicit consent.</p>
        <p>We don't offer refunds for partial months. If you cancel mid-period, you keep access until the period ends but we don't pro-rate the remainder. If you've been charged in error or experienced a service failure on our end, email us and we'll sort it out.</p>
        <p>Prices may change for new sign-ups. We won't change the price for existing subscribers without at least 30 days' notice via email.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Termination</h2>
        <p>You can cancel and delete your account at any time. We may suspend or terminate your account if you breach these Terms, if we're legally required to, or if the service is being discontinued.</p>
        <p>If we discontinue the service entirely, we'll give at least 60 days' notice and provide a way to export your data before shutdown.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Disclaimers and limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>ClubShed is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We don't guarantee that the service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or suitable for every specific purpose.</p>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability to you for any claim arising out of or relating to the service is limited to the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim. We're not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages (lost profits, lost data beyond what's reasonably recoverable from our backups, business interruption, etc.).</p>
        <p>None of the above excludes liability for things that can't be excluded by law (such as fraud or gross negligence in jurisdictions where those carve-outs apply).</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>The ClubShed name, logo, website, and software are owned by Lucas Seewald. The content you create in ClubShed (equipment lists, photos, reports) is owned by you.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Changes to these Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will be communicated to account holders by email at least 30 days before they take effect. Continued use of the service after changes take effect means you accept the updated Terms. If you don't accept them, you can cancel your account.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Governing law and disputes</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the law of Spain. Any disputes that can't be resolved by direct conversation will be brought before the competent courts in Spain. If you're a consumer in the EU, you also have the protections of your local consumer law and the right to bring claims in your country of residence.</p>
        <p>Before going legal, please email <a href="mailto:hello@clubshed.pro">hello@clubshed.pro</a>. Almost every dispute we've heard of in SaaS could have been resolved by a conversation. We'd rather have the conversation.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-page__section">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:hello@clubshed.pro">hello@clubshed.pro</a>.</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem) 0 clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem);
  }
  .legal-page .container {
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .legal-page__header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .legal-page__header .tag {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-page__header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-page__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .legal-page__section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .legal-page__section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .legal-page__section p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 66ch;
  }
  .legal-page__section ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 1.25rem;
    max-width: 66ch;
  }
  .legal-page__section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .legal-page__section strong {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .legal-page__section a {
    color: var(--kit-orange);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>
